The Kowloon Jade Clerk commission has identified forged cairn tablets circulating in the Measure's Rest archive that misrepresent historical toll precedents in ways that benefit current Red Sand Accounts territorial claims. The Kowloon postmaster requires a physical specimen for the commission's authentication analysis before the precedents can be legally challenged. Recover one forged tablet and return it for examination.
The forged cairn tablet has been delivered to the Kowloon postmaster and forwarded to the Jade Clerk commission for analysis. The examination confirmed that the forgery was executed with Synod ritual inscription tools, providing a direct evidentiary link between the Synod network and the Red Sand Accounts territory disputes. The authentication report has been transmitted to the Mafdet Ledger House commission for inclusion in the pending territorial review.

